quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  2,154,"And do not say of those who are slain in the way of Allah, \"they are dead.\" In fact, they are alive but you do not perceive that life"
  2,155,"We will surely put you to trial by involving you in fear and hunger and by causing loss of property, life and earnings. And give good tidings to those who remain steadfast in these trials"
  2,156,"when a misfortune comes to them, they say, \"We are Allah's and we shall certainly return to Him"
  2,157,Their Lord will bestow great blessings and mercy upon them; such are the people who are rightly guided
  2,158,"Indeed Safa and Marwah are among the emblems of Allah: it is, therefore, no sin for him, who performs Hajj or `Umrah to the House of AIIah, to run between the two hills; and Allah knows and appreciates him who does any good with a willing heart"
  2,159,"Indeed Allah curses, and the cursers, too, curse those who conceal the clear teachings and guidance We have sent down, after We have made these plain in the Book for the guidance of all mankind"
  2,160,"I, however, will forgive those of them who repent of it, mend their ways and make own what they were concealing: for I am very generous in accepting repentance and showing mercy"
  2,161,"Those who adopted the way of disbelief and died as disbelievers, are accursed of Allah and of angels and of all mankind: they shall remain accursed for ever"
  2,162,"Their punishment shall not be lightened, nor shall they be reprieved"
  2,163,"Your Deity is Allah alone: there is no deity save the All-Beneficent and All-Merciful Allah"